        </div>

        <!-- body -->
        <div class="featured__body">
          <div class="featured__pill">Featured · Patent-Filed</div>
          <h3 class="featured__title">Battery Passport <em>&amp; on-device fault intelligence</em></h3>
          <p class="featured__desc">
            A patent-filed system that fuses <strong style="color:var(--text)">deep learning, swarm optimization and electrochemistry</strong> to estimate the state of an EV battery — its charge, health and degradation — directly on the BMS, in real time, without ever needing labeled data. Built at Suavy Technologies for use in battery swapping stations.
          </p>

          <div class="featured__params">
            <div class="lbl">Estimated parameters · Equivalent Circuit Model</div>
            <div class="params">
              <span>R0</span><span>R1</span><span>R2</span><span>C1</span><span>C2</span><span>η</span><span>M0</span><span>M</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <ul class="featured__highlights">
            <li><strong>Hybrid pipeline.</strong> ANN delivers fast initial parameter prediction; PSO refines them against measured terminal-voltage residuals — combining speed with precision.</li>
            <li><strong>Physics-informed core.</strong> The model isn't a black box. It is anchored to a 2-RC Thévenin equivalent circuit, ensuring estimates remain physically plausible across temperature and aging.</li>
            <li><strong>No labels needed.</strong> Self-supervised pipeline learns directly from voltage / current / temperature streams — solving the dataset bottleneck that blocks most BMS ML work.</li>
            <li><strong>Lifecycle &amp; warranty.</strong> Outputs are cryptographically sealed in a tamper-resistant Battery Passport — enabling fleet-level safety, second-life tracking and warranty enforcement.</li>
            <li><strong>Real-time fault signal.</strong> Drift in estimated parameters acts as an early-warning signal for cell degradation, internal short, and capacity fade.</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="featured__stack">
            <span>Python</span><span>TensorFlow</span><span>NumPy</span><span>SciPy / PSO</span><span>MATLAB</span><span>ECM</span>
          </div>

          <a href="https://github.com/saurabhpandey2108" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" class="btn btn--ghost">View Related Work <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

